📋 Lab Overview

This lab focuses on physically connecting a multi-tier network topology using the appropriate cable types.
You are given a pre-built logical diagram with labeled links between routers, switches, and end devices, and must wire them correctly — without relying on Packet Tracer's Auto MDI-X feature.


🎯 Objectives

Connect all network devices according to the labeled topology
Select the correct cable type for each link (straight-through, crossover, fiber)
Understand when to use single-mode vs. multimode fiber based on distance
Practice cable selection as if Auto MDI-X is disabled
